<H1>Status of the ERA-40 Re-Analysis Archive at the BADC</H1>
<I>This page is updated monthly to inform users of the current 
status of ERA-40 at the BADC.</I>

<HR ALIGN=LEFT>

<H2>Introduction</H2>

<P>The BADC is extracting ECMWF <a href="/data/ecmwf-e40/">ERA-40 Re-analysis data</a> 
on a daily basis to keep pace (with a slight delay) with production. The data is 
currently being copied into two separate archives: 
<UL>
<LI>The <a href="#badc">standard BADC data archive</a> (at the Rutherford Appleton Laboratory, Oxfordshire)</LI>
<LI>An <a href="#manchester">archive at the Manchester High-Performance Computing Centre</a> (maintained and 
updated by CGAM (Centre for Global Atmospheric Modelling) at the University of Reading).</LI>
</UL>
<P>
The reason for holding two separate data archives is to meet the requirements of two 
distinct groups of atmospheric (and other) scientists. The standard BADC archive will 
serve the data using formats and utilities that the majority of earth scientists can 
make use of. The Manchester archive, on the other hand, is aimed specifically at users 
of the modelling resources held on the high-performance computing systems. This data 
will be mainly used by members of UGAMP (the UK universities Global Atmospheric Modelling 
Programme). This page gives an overview of the contents and the current 
status of each archive. 
<P>
Links are also provided to <A HREF="#validation">validation information relating to ERA-40</A> and 
a <A HREF="/data/ecmwf-e40/news.html">latest news page for ERA-40</A>.
<P>
<HR ALIGN=LEFT>

